headline: Chubb (CB) Margin Declines to 16.5%, Challenging Bullish Narratives on Profit Quality
summary: Chubb (CB) posted a net profit margin of 16.5%, down from 18.3% a year ago, and annual earnings growth over the past five years has averaged 12.7%. However, the most recent year results turned negative. Looking ahead, earnings are forecast to rise at just 2.3% per year compared to the broader US market’s 15.5% pace, and revenue is projected to slip by 1.8% annually over the next three years. Despite these near-term pressures, the shares stand out for their value relative to the industry,...
